Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
place_partition_clone(25.10)                      place_partition_clone(25.10)

Name
       place_partition_clone  -  Places  the clones, set their orientation and
       syncs up the data with other hierarchical instances (master and clones)
       of the same module

Syntax
       place_partition_clone

       [-help]

       -hinst <partition_clone_hinst_name>

       -location {<x y>}

       [-orient {R0 R180 MX MY}]

       [-skip_sync]

       [-sync_objs {placeBlockage routeBlockage pinBlockage macros fences}]

       Places the clones, set their orientation and syncs  up  the  data  with
       other hierarchical instances (master and clones) of the same module.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each place_partition_clone parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man place_partition_clone

       -hinst <partition_clone_hinst_name>
              Specifies the name of partition clone hierarchical instance.

              Data_type: string, required

       -location {<x y>}
              Specifies location of the clone partition.

              Data_type: point, required

       -orient {R0 R180 MX MY}
              Specifies orientation of the clone  partition.  The  orientation
              can be one of the following: R0, R180, MX, and MY

              Data_type: enum, optional

       -skip_sync
              When  specified,  the  tool skips the sync-up of reference hinst
              (-hinst) objects with other hinsts of the same module.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -sync_objs {placeBlockage routeBlockage pinBlockage macros fences}
              When specified, the tool does the sync-up of the  specified  ob-
              jects from reference hinst with other hinsts of same module. The
              objects that can be synced up include placeBlockage, routeBlock-
              age, pinBlockage, macros, and  fences.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
       Hinst: A1 (master), A2 (clone), A3(clone), A4 (clone)

              * The following commands places the clone A2 at location 2,5. If
                partition  block  has FP/def/route objs/data present, the com-
                mand will sync the data from A2 to all other hinsts (A1  (mas-
                ter), A3 , A4 (clones)).

                place_partition_clones -hinst A2 -location {2 5}

              * The  following  commands places the clone A3 at location 12,15
                and changes the orientation to R180 (if not already R180).  If
                partition  block  has FP/def/route objs/data present, the com-
                mand will sync the data from A3 to all other hinsts (A1  (mas-
                ter), A2 , A4 (clones))

                place_partition_clones  -hinst  A3  -location  {12 15} -orient
                R180

              * The following commands places the master A1 at location 22,25.
                If partition block has  FP/def/route  objs/data  present,  the
                command  will  sync  the data from A1 to all other hinsts (A2,
                A3, A4 (clones)).

                place_partition_clones -hinst A1 -location {22 25}

              * The following commands places the master A1 at location 22,25.
                If partition block has  FP/def/route  objs/data  present,  the
                command will not sync any data to other hinsts.

                place_partition_clones -hinst A1 -location {22 25} -skip_sync

              * The  following  commands places the clone A3 at location 12,15
                and changes the orientation to R180 (if not already R180).  If
                partition  block  has FP/def/route objs/data present, the com-
                mand will not sync any data to other hinsts.

                place_partition_clones -hinst A3  -location  {12  15}  -orient
                R180 -skip_sync

              * The  following  commands places the clone A3 at location 12,15
                and changes the orientation to R180 (if not already R180).  If
                partition  block  has FP/def/route objs/data present, the com-
                mand will sync the bus-guide data from A3 to all other  hinsts
                (A1 (master), A2 , A4 (clones)).

                place_partition_clones  -hinst  A3  -location  {12 15} -orient
                R180 -sync_obj {bus_guide}

